-- Colombian Stock Movers: Tableros & Maderas, Bolsa de Valores
-- B y   C h r i s t i n e   J e n k i n s
-- 2012-04-17T22:01:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-17/colombian-stock-movers-tableros-maderas-bolsa-de-valores.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close of trading.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  rose 0.3 percent to 15,180.66, while the
Colcap Index increased 0.3 percent to 1,765.55.  Tableros & Maderas de Caldas SA  (TABLEMA CB), a wood
products maker, advanced 1.9 percent to 10.50 pesos. Investors
are anticipating an increase in production after the opening of
a new plant this month, said Carlos Eduardo Gonzalez, an analyst
at brokerage Bolsa y Renta. Juan Fernando Vasquez, the company’s
president, said a new medium-density fiberboards, or MDF, plant
would have its first boards ready at the beginning of April in
an  interview  published on March 27 by the daily El Colombiano.  Bolsa de Valores de Colombia SA  (BVC CB), the operator of
the country’s main stock exchange, increased 1.8 percent to
34.50 pesos. The company rose after saying net income increased
40 percent to 11.5 billion pesos ($6.5 million) in the first
three months of the year on its  website  yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Christine Jenkins in New York at 
